Image shadow and border.

Added the following to style-zero.css

.img-shadow {
   margin: 10px;
   float:right;
   background: url(../images/trans-shadow.png) no-repeat bottom right;
}

.img-shadow img {
    display: block; /* IE won't do well without this */
    background-color: #fff; /* Background color of the border created by the padding */
    border: 1px solid #cecece; /* A 1 pixel greyish border is applied to the white border created by the padding */
    margin: -6px 6px 6px -6px;
    padding: 5px;
    float: left;
}

.img-shadow p {
    padding: -6px 6px 6px -6px;
    text-align: center;
    font-style: italic;


Save the CSS, and call it in your webpage file through the following HTML codes.

<div class="img-shadow">
  <img src="images/fitzroy.jpg" alt="My picture alt" title="My picture title" />
  <p>Every picture deserves a good caption. Thankfully with this method you can give it one.</p>
</div>
